law.text:
This subtitle does not apply to:
The following persons when engaged in the regular course of their respective businesses and professions:
An attorney at law;
An escrow agent;
A certified public accountant;
A banking institution, other-state bank, national banking association, credit union, or savings and loan association;
A person that:
Provides bill payer services, as defined in § 12-401 of this title;
Does not initiate any contract with individual creditors of the debtor to compromise a debt or arrange a new payment schedule; and
Does not provide any debt counseling services;
A person that provides accelerated mortgage payment services, as defined in § 12-401 of this title;
A title insurer, title insurance agency, or abstract company; or
A judicial officer or a person acting under a court order;
A person while performing services incidental to the dissolution, winding up, or liquidation of a partnership, corporation, or other business enterprise;
A trade or mercantile association acting in the course of arranging the adjustment of debts with a business establishment; or
A mortgage lender, as defined in § 11-501 of this article, that:
Is licensed by the Commissioner; and
Does not receive funds from a consumer for the purpose of distributing the funds among the consumer's creditors in full or partial payment of the consumer's debts.
